STEP|79|**`encodeDocument(content, title)`** — Markdown docs → typed TOON records (D\|decision, K\|task, C\|config, G\|goal, X\|context, T\|text). Section headers (#,##) become record types.
STEP|80|**`encodeMemory(content, agentId)`** — Agent MEMORY.md → M\|section\|key\|value records. Parses headings into sections, key-value pairs into structured entries, bullets into items.
STEP|81|**`encodePrompt(prompt)`** — Detects structured patterns (numbered lists → L\|, bullets, key-value blocks → K\|, tables → T\|) and encodes them. Falls back to `abbreviateText()` for freeform.
STEP|82|replace(/\\\\\\\|/g, '\|') // BROKEN: the pipe is the regex OR operator
STEP|83|Root cause:** The encoder produces only single-backslash escapes (`\\|`, `\n`). The decoder's attempt to also handle double-backslash escapes (`\\\|`, `\\n`) added a regex with wrong backslash count. 
STEP|84|Fix:** Remove the double-escape handlers entirely. Only keep:
STEP|85|Verification:** Test `decodeToonResponse('T\|Context\|0\|test')` → must return `'Context \| 0 \| test'`, NOT `'\|C\|o\|n\|t\|e\|x\|t\| \| \|0\| \| \|t\|e\|s\|t\|'`.
STEP|86|Impact:** Any agent memory containing pipe chars (markdown tables, code) produces unparseable M\| records.
STEP|87|Proposed fix for v2:** Use a non-pipe delimiter (null byte, record separator) or base64-encode content fields.
STEP|88|Fix:** The Claude route must build a combined system prompt from ALL outputs:
STEP|89|Fix:** Replaced with `encodeDocument()` and `encodeMemory()` calls. Now produces real `T\|header\|idx\|abbreviated_text` and `M\|section\|key\|value` records.
STEP|90|Why:** Word-abbreviation only swaps ~150 words. Most text passes through unchanged. TOON record prefixes (`T\|MARC\|0\|`) add overhead. The original 84.5% claim came from `toon.dense()` applied to STR
STEP|91|To reach 78-85%:**
STEP|92|**Layer 1 — Structure stripping** (32% — BUILT, not wired): Strip formatting from all docs
STEP|93|**Layer 2 — Schema-based encoding** (40% on structured data — EXISTS in `toon.ts`, not wired): Detect data blocks in prompts, apply `toon.dense()`
STEP|94|**Layer 3 — CIE data filtering** (84.5% on filtered queries — EXISTS in `src/cie/`): Only send relevant fields to the LLM
STEP|95|**Layer 4 — Reference-based injection** (95% for context — NOT BUILT): Inject doc IDs not content; resolve on demand
STEP|96|`toon-format` — TOON compression format, bidirectional benchmarks, adaptive injection
STEP|97|`yvon-os-development` — YVON OS internal development patterns
STEP|98|`hermes-agent` — Hermes agent framework, CLI, memory, skills
